observations.recommendation:
Municipal Mayor ensures that the GSO or the authorized property custodian prepare the Report on Local Road Networks and maintain the local road inventory, road map and property cards for all roads and their components; 

Municipal Mayor ensures that the Inventory Committee conduct physical count of LRN and render the required Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network; and 

Municipal Mayor ensures that the Municipal Accountant comply with the required template in preparation of LRNLC as required in the Circular.

Municipal Treasurer submits to the Audit Team the detailed ledger of the amount receivable from MACWAS consumers totaling ₱6,979,800.84 for further evaluation;

Municipal Treasurer makes a detailed monitoring of income receivables from all exchange transactions; and 

Municipal Treasurer furnishes such monitoring of income receivables to the Office of the Municipal Accountant every year-end for the purpose of preparing a yearly accrual of these receivables.

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials establish ways to improve the cash position such as, but not limited to, efficient revenue collection and adoption of effective austerity measures; 

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials  review, prioritize and update the programs, activities and projects taking into consideration the total cash available for their implementation; 

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials hire qualified personnel to perform the monitoring and reconciliation duties; 

Municipal Mayor instructs the Municipal Budget and Accounting Offices to conduct periodic reconciliation of records within and between these offices; and 

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials regularly review the continuing appropriation balances as part of the annual budget preparation to ensure that these have valid and sufficient fund sources.

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials submit a written explanation for the non-implementation of the minimum organizational structure and staffing pattern for the Office of the Municipal Assessor;



Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials initiate steps towards the revision of the approved plantilla of personnel taking into consideration the minimum organizational structure and staffing pattern of the Office of the Municipal Assessor in compliance with Section 472 of RA No. 7160 and Chapter I, Section 5 of the Manual on Real Property Appraisal and Assessment Operations; and 

Municipal Mayor directs the HRMO to initiate steps towards the hiring, reassignment, and transfer of personnel to the Office of the Municipal Assessor with the end in view of filling-in the minimum organizational structure and staffing pattern.

Municipal Mayor ceases designation of casual personnel as revenue collectors;


Municipal Mayor directs the Municipal Treasurer to determine the total manpower needs of her Office especially the total additional revenue collectors; 

Municipal Mayor initiates steps towards the revision of the approved plantilla of personnel taking into consideration the manpower needs of the Office of the Municipal Treasurer; and

Municipal Mayor directs the HRMO to initiate steps towards the hiring, reassignment and transfer of personnel to fill the vacant positions of the treasury office in accordance with civil service rules and in compliance with DBM LBC No. 137.

Incorporate the previous years’ unexpended balance of LDRRMF totaling ₱2.410 million in the LDRRMFIP;


Maintain and submit the Trust Liability-DRRM subsidiary ledgers for transfers of agency’s unutilized DRRMF-MOOE to the special trust fund by year of transfer;

That the LDRRMO and Municipal Budget Office allocate the QRF or stand-by fund for relief and recovery programs as lump sum.

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials initiate steps towards the revision of the plantilla of personnel taking into consideration the additional manpower needs of all departments and offices of the Municipality; 

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials ensure that the HRMO initiate steps towards filling existing vacancies based on the revised plantilla, especially the vacant department head positions, with the end in view of maximizing the organizational structure; 

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials hire casual personnel in accordance with the provisions of Section 9.g of the revised 2017 ORAOHRA;

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials hire Job Order workers only for the purpose of implementing local projects in accordance with Section 77 of RA No. 7160; and

Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials consider designating personnel in compliance with the revised 2017 ORAOHRA.

Use the prescribed account titles prescribed under COA Circular No. 2015-009;

Recognize the proper RPT/SET receivables and deferred income accounts and discounts for advance and prompt payments upon collection;

Make the necessary adjustments by following the proposed adjusting journal entries in Annex E; and

Submit the revised and supplemental LDRRMFIP reflecting the above-mentioned changes in expenditures purpose with the approval of the Local Sanggunian;

Incorporate the previous years’ unexpended balance of LDRRMF totaling ₱2.410 million in the LDRRMFIP;

Maintain and submit the Trust Liability-DRRM subsidiary ledgers for transfers of agency’s unutilized DRRMF-MOOE to the special trust fund by year of transfer;

That the LDRRMO and Municipal Budget Office allocate the QRF or stand-by fund for relief and recovery programs as lump sum; and

Utilize the LDRRM funds for the specific purpose for which they  were created and refrain from incurring and charging expenses that do not contribute to the advancement of LDRRM objectives.

We recommended that Management:
Establish ways to improve the cash position such as, but not limited to, efficient revenue collection and adoption of effective austerity measures;
Review, prioritize and update the programs, activities and projects taking into consideration the total cash available for their implementation;
Hire qualified personnel to perform the monitoring and reconciliation duties;
Instruct the Municipal Budget and Accounting Offices to conduct periodic reconciliation of records within and between these offices; and
Regularly review the continuing appropriation balances as part of the annual budget preparation to ensure that these have valid and sufficient fund sources.

We recommended and Municipal Mayor and other concerned officials agreed to:
Initiate steps towards the revision of the plantilla of personnel taking into consideration the additional manpower needs of all departments and offices of the Municipality;
Ensure that the HRMO initiate steps towards filling existing vacancies based on the revised plantilla, especially the vacant department head positions, with the end in view of maximizing the organizational structure;
Hire casual personnel in accordance with the provisions of Section 9.g of the revised 2017 ORAOHRA;
Hire Job Order workers only for the purpose of implementing local projects in accordance with Section 77 of RA No. 7160; and
Consider designating personnel in compliance with the revised 2017 ORAOHRA.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Cease designation of casual personnel as revenue collectors;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to determine the total manpower needs of her Office especially the total additional revenue collectors;
Initiate steps towards the revision of the approved plantilla of personnel taking into consideration the manpower needs of the Office of the Municipal Treasurer; and
Direct the HRMO to initiate steps towards the hiring, reassignment and transfer of personnel to fill the vacant positions of the treasury office in accordance with civil service rules and in compliance with DBM LBC No. 137.

We recommended that Management direct:
The Municipal Treasurer	to prepare a schedule of unreleased/unclaimed checks at the end of the reporting period and submit thereafter to the Municipal Accountant, and;
The Municipal Accountant to post adjustment in the books of accounts that correspond to the unreleased or unclaimed checks at every end of the reporting period.

We recommended Management to:
Strictly adhere to the guidelines set under of RA 10121, COA Circular No. 2012-002 and Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1 dated March 25, 2013. Further, strictly adhere to the existing rules and regulations on providing complete documentation of claims against government funds and ensure that funds of the government are safeguarded from improper disposition;
Refrain from charging expenses against the LDRRMF which are not related to and do not support disaster risk management activities.

We recommended and agreed that Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
a.  Strictly observe compliance with the perpetual inventory method of accounting on the supplies and materials procured for construction projects by administration by recording all purchases under the Construction Materials Inventory account;
b. Prepare and maintain ledger cards, supplies ledger card per stock number, use the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued as the basis of recognizing supplies and materials expense, and reconcile its inventory accounts with the actual physical count semi-annually;
Coordinate with the Municipal Engineer for utilized and issued construction materials to projects or activities; and
Effect the necessary adjustment for the amount of supplies and materials which remained unutilized.
